<div class="c230_129">
<div id="v230.129.1"><span class="H7892 s">A Song</span><span class="H4609 s"> of degrees</span><span class="H7227 s">. Many a time</span><span class="H6887 s"> have they afflicted</span><span class="H5271 s"> me from my youth</span><span class="H3478 s">, may Israel</span><span class="H559 s"> now say</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Many…: or, Much)</span></div>
<div id="v230.129.2"><span class="H7227 s">Many a time</span><span class="H6887 s"> have they afflicted</span><span class="H5271 s"> me from my youth</span><span class="H3201 s">: yet they have not prevailed</span> against me. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Many…: or, Much)</span></div>
<div id="v230.129.3"><span class="H2790 s">The plowers</span><span class="H2790 s"> plowed</span><span class="H1354 s"> upon my back</span><span class="H748 s">: they made long</span><span class="H4618 s"> their furrows</span><span class="H4618 s"> †</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.129.4"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H6662 s"> <i>is</i> righteous</span><span class="H7112 s">: he hath cut asunder</span><span class="H5688 s"> the cords</span><span class="H7563 s"> of the wicked</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.129.5"><span class="H954 s">Let them all be confounded</span><span class="H5472 s"> and turned</span><span class="H268 s"> back</span><span class="H8130 s"> that hate</span><span class="H6726 s"> Zion</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.129.6"><span class="H2682 s">Let them be as the grass</span><span class="H1406 s"> <i>upon</i> the housetops</span><span class="H3001 s">, which withereth</span><span class="H6927 s"> afore</span><span class="H8025 s"> it groweth up</span>:</div>
<div id="v230.129.7"><span class="H7114 s">Wherewith the mower</span><span class="H4390 s"> filleth</span><span class="H3709 s"> not his hand</span><span class="H6014 s">; nor he that bindeth sheaves</span><span class="H2683 s"> his bosom</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.129.8"><span class="H5674 s">Neither do they which go by</span><span class="H559 s"> say</span><span class="H1293 s">, The blessing</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H1288 s"> <i>be</i> upon you: we bless</span><span class="H8034 s"> you in the name</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span>.</div></div>
